<br>
The only difference, I think, is that Elven Blades admitted an evil (race) -while- they were still members of the Fellowship.  As far as I know, Winds of Destiny (and others in the past) left the Fellowship -before- admitting members that would invalidate their membership in the Fellowship based on its charter.  In fact the Elven Blades reignation letter was only hastily penned and posted after a couple of their members &quot;went public&quot; with the inclusion of that individual.  For some (in and out of the Fellowship) the speculation was how long would they &quot;hide&quot; the inclusion of evils (directly against the Fellowship charter) while still visibly remaining a member of the Fellowship and what that does to the reputation of the Fellowship.  That is only the link to the Fellowship, the guild's membership in a larger organisation can reflect on that organisation.  The rest is entirely within their own guild. <p><center><table width="55%"><tr><td align="center">
